General Summary:
We are seeking a creative, curious, and adaptable early-career analyst to join our People Analytics team. As a Business Intelligence Analyst I (the second level in a five-tier Business Intelligence career path), you will perform foundational data reporting, analysis, and insight generation, working in systems like Workday, Tableau, and ServiceNow. In this role, you will collaborate with fellow BIAs, HR Business Partners, HR leaders, and cross-functional teams to enable data-driven talent decisions within our People & Communications organization and across the enterprise.

Principal Duties and Responsibilities
• Conduct data profiling and analysis to evaluate data sources to determine the best source for business information
• Acquiring, transforming and translating data into actionable dashboards, reports, algorithms or datasets with minimal support from mentor and manager
• Performing statistical analysis and presenting findings to guide and advise leadership
• Collaborate with data engineers to perform data validation and testing activities as appropriate
• Continuously develop and build upon existing knowledge of the insurance industry
• Continuously develop and build upon existing knowledge of data stored in company databases
• Works directly with internal customers to refine requirements and validate output to ensure solutions will meet expectations

Job Specifications
• Bachelors Degree preferred, and/or equivalent experience
• 2+ years experience with demonstrated success at an Associate level in a data analytics related field
• Knowledge of analytics programming languages (SQL/R/Python)
• Experience with modern BI toolsets (Tableau, Alteryx, PowerBI, or equivalent)
• Understanding of data profiling, statistical analysis and data modeling concepts
• Comfortable extracting and leveraging data out of data warehouse, transactional databases, object stores & API based environments
• Demonstrated ability to translate business needs into technical solutions
• Ability to embrace change, adapt to the unexpected, and focus energies, people, and solutions on practical and positive results
• Demonstrated problem solving skills
• Strong communications skills
• Aptitude and drive to learn new technologies and analysis techniques
• Strong team player; able to work effectively within a team and more broadly with people from a variety of backgrounds and areas across the organization.
• Experience/certification in Workday a plus
• Experience with HR analytics or HR functional areas a plus

job_description:
We are seeking a Business Intelligence Analyst to support Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) reporting within an enterprise Data & Analytics organization. This role partners closely with product, operations, and technology stakeholders to design and deliver high-impact operational and transactional insights. The ideal candidate blends strong technical BI expertise with the ability to translate complex product data into clear, actionable reporting.

Worksite Location: Eden Prairie, MN (Mon-Thurs in-office; Friday WFH)

Pay Range:
• up to $121K base salary + annual bonus + profit sharing bonus + 401k + pension
• No work visa sponsorship available; no C2C, thank you

Benefits:
• Base salary + bonus potential
• Medical, dental, vision
• Pension plan
• Profit sharing
• 401(k)
• Relocation assistance
• paid personal time (PTO)
• FREE two-year community/technical college tuition for children of employees, and more

Roles & Responsibilities
• Partner with PLM functional and technical teams to understand end-to-end product lifecycle processes and translate business needs into reporting solutions
• Elicit, document, and refine reporting requirements through stakeholder collaboration and iterative feedback cycles
• Design, build, test, and deploy operational and transactional dashboards and reports supporting product development, change management, and product data governance
• Own PLM reporting initiatives, proactively identifying opportunities to improve transparency, automation, and data quality across product processes
• Troubleshoot, enhance, and maintain existing BI assets, ensuring accuracy, performance, and alignment with evolving business requirements
• Ensure reporting solutions meet performance expectations and incorporate automation where appropriate (scheduled delivery, bursting, or event-based distribution)
• Develop analyses and dashboards using PLM-related subject areas with a focus on usability, scalability, and performance
• Create intuitive filters, prompts, and drill-through functionality to support both standard and ad-hoc analysis
• Configure scheduled delivery and automated distribution of reports and dashboards
• Build and optimize BI data models using complex SQL across PLM and related enterprise data sources
• Develop formatted reports aligned to product structures, engineering changes, and development milestones
• Tune queries and reporting solutions to ensure reliable performance on small-to-medium data sets

Required Skills & Experience
• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, or a related field, or equivalent professional experience
• 4+ years of experience designing and developing within a business intelligence/reporting tool like OTBI, BI Publisher, Oracle Business Intelligence Enterprise Edition (OBIEE), Oracle Analytics Server, or Oracle Analytics Cloud
• 4+ years of experience designing and delivering solutions within enterprise BI and reporting platforms in support of Product Lifecycle Management reporting and analytics use cases
• Strong ability to gather technical and business requirements and own BI solutions from concept through production
• Experience facilitating discussions, leading working sessions, or coordinating delivery efforts across teams
• Proven analytical thinking, problem-solving, and decision-making skills
• Strong organizational skills with the ability to manage multiple priorities effectively
• Clear, confident written and verbal communication skills with technical and non-technical audiences
• Authorization to work in the United States without current or future employer sponsorship

Preferred Skills & Experience
• Advanced SQL expertise, including analytical and window functions
• Prior exposure to cloud-based PLM platforms and their underlying data models (e.g., item master, BOMs, engineering changes)
• Experience with SQL performance tuning and optimization
• Working knowledge of data governance, master data management, or product data stewardship practices

General Description
The Senior Business Intelligence Analyst is responsible for analyzing, developing and enhancing the operation of all aspects of a college-wide data lake and business intelligence support. The primary role is to assemble and transform data into actionable knowledge for the use of college leaders and administrators including: executive level reports and dashboards; designing, building, and normalizing data and data bases and locating and extracting data from the College’s enterprise systems and other internal and external data resources. The Business Intelligence Analyst is responsible for creating, implementing and maintaining data lakes and business intelligence applications and databases.

College Intro
Success starts at Community College of Philadelphia. Innovators and difference makers work at Community College of Philadelphia. Diversity thrives at Community College of Philadelphia. We are a college that is committed to promoting a work environment that attracts and retains talented and diverse faculty and staff. We challenge each other and ourselves to achieve at the highest level while contributing to the mission of the College and the betterment of Philadelphia. We value and support an intellectually dynamic community to prepare our students for global citizenship. Join us and become a part of a community that has long been and will continue to be generators of generational chance in this city and beyond.

Community College of Philadelphia is an open-admission, associate-degree-granting institution which provides access to higher education for all who may benefit. Its programs of study in the liberal arts and sciences, career technologies, and basic academic skills provide a coherent foundation for college transfer, employment and lifelong learning. The College serves Philadelphia by preparing its students to be informed and concerned citizens, active participants in the cultural life of the city, and enabled to meet the changing needs of business, industry and the professions. To help address broad economic, cultural and political concerns in the city and beyond, the College draws together students from a wide range of ages and backgrounds and seeks to provide the programs and support they need to achieve their goals.

Specific Responsibilities
• Prepares reporting, analytics, and dashboard development from concept to implementation.
• Analyzes, develops and interprets data needs for end users.
• Assists in development, implementation, and maintenance of the enterprise-wide systems and data warehouse solutions.
• Serves as a resource to all levels of management for reviewing, analyzing, designing/creating, and implementing institutional reports, dashboards and data warehouse solutions.
• Provides training and documentation on reporting systems and solutions as needed for all levels of staff.
• Understands conceptual and physical data models using relational and dimensional data modeling techniques.
• Maintains system storage structures for warehousing system needed for reporting solutions.
• Deliver quality customer services to both internal and external constituents in a professional, helpful and courteous manner.
• Perform established maintenance tasks to keep the reporting platform going, including license management, data bridge service management, validation of scheduled refreshes, etc
• Performs other duties as assigned.

• Ability to carry out assigned responsibilities with minimal supervision required.

• Ability to maintain sensitivity, understanding and respect for a diverse academic environment, inclusive of students, faculty, and staff of varying social, economic, cultural, ideological, and ethnic backgrounds required.

Preferred Qualifications
• Master’s degree is preferred. Any and all must be from a recognized institutional accreditor.
• Extensive experience in Ellucian’s suite of products preferred.
• Knowledge and/or experience with PL/SQL, HTML, XML, and Java preferred.
• Knowledge of data modeling, star schema, and denormalized data models preferred.
• Experience with Ellucian’s Banner system, Operational Data Store or Enterprise Data Warehouse and Amazon Web Services preferred.
